<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-B4CAA874-AEF6-4292-ACF9-46930A729737" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-B4CAA874-AEF6-4292-ACF9-46930A729737" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">04 The process of the Nozzle Failure detection, Nozzle Failure Compensation and PAINt</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M149114-B174"><p class="- topic/p ">This document gives a description of Nozzle Failure detection , Nozzle Failure Compensation (NFC) and PAINt (Piezo sensing Acoustics Inkjet chaNnels in time domain). 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-B22FF536-33DE-421D-B037-1CF2B24071B3" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Short description </title><table id="GUID-0CBCD16A-ED42-4144-9201-8FEDC6460DCE" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Nozzle failure detection 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-E7BCD18C-96DC-452A-AD94-6577E0EDDF24" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">PAINt</title><image href="GUID-016EB9C4-7861-49D5-857C-0137C0CA1125-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-016EB9C4-7861-49D5-857C-0137C0CA1125-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">PAINt (piezo element in printhead) is listening 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Always up to date 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Used to decide on maintenance actions 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Identifies between Electrical, Air or Dirt failures of the nozzle 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Works proper after a printhead calibration 
</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5CEB0904-E185-4BED-86CF-739ADF5BA0CB" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">M&amp;C unit</title><image href="GUID-01F1E791-B1C2-47FE-9374-C4B7F3EFF35A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-01F1E791-B1C2-47FE-9374-C4B7F3EFF35A-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">M&amp;C unit is measuring 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">On demand triggered by the operator (nozzle optimization) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Nozzle status is static (info from the last nozzle optimization) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Used to find nozzle failures that a not detected by PAINt 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Identifies between Mis-directed / Non jetting nozzle failures of the nozzle 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Works reliable after a proper engine calibration 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Works reliable when used with correct media settings 
</p></li></ul></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p ">The Nozzle failure information for each printhead is available in SDS test 04-6-002 Get nozzle status: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">. 
</p><fig id="GUID-91AF0FFD-AE2C-4C30-B7F8-DCDD7D936E01" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-D07724B4-D477-4F67-8801-3DB5E3494AEE-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D07724B4-D477-4F67-8801-3DB5E3494AEE-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The test results are used to define further repair actions. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Examples: M&amp;C unit / Maintenance unit / Automatic Maintenance / Printhead calibration / ... 
</p><table id="GUID-3B153475-1D97-4734-80DA-0E8F0BDBF9E0" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Nozzle failure Compensation 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Compensation: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If a nozzle needs to fire and the nozzle has a failure, the printer tries to use another nozzle to fire on (almost) the same position on media 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Goal: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Reduce the number of wrong colored lines on the print as much as possible. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The more printing passes, the better the chance of a successful compensation of a failing nozzle. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="M149114-B175" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Extended description</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">PAINt</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">During this automated NFC process, the piezo actuator hits the UVgel ink in each channel with a minor mechanical signal at each carriage turn. This signal is too weak to create a real droplet but strong enough to create a vibration in the UVgel ink. Then the response of this vibration is measured with the piezo actuator. In this way the software can measure whether a nozzle is working correctly. This process of this nozzle failure detection is called PAINt (Piezo sensing Acoustics Inkjet chaNnels in time domain). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">PAINt actions are automatically performed: 
</p><ul id="UL_C35D7A9360FA41C0A32CB5D404B70284" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_9A4445FCE8344F099C155A89BCDC7994" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">during initialization of the engine 
</p></li><li id="LI_E4821CA7FF7D4EC0AA873FDFA3D3F45F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">at start of a print action after each print swath 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">After a PAINt action, the response is analyzed. Each individual nozzle gets a PAINT classification. Several nozzle fail causes (electrical, air, dirt) can be detected by PAINt. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Based on (changes in) the amount of nozzles per classification, engine software decides how to continue e.g. resume printing, abort printing (in case paper touch), create pressure pulse to "rinse" all nozzle channels, create an error message and so on. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">All nozzle are being classified into 3 categories as follows. 
</p><table id="M149114-TB176" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="stage" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="60*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="50.50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">NFC classification 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Output result without Nozzle Failure Correction (NFC) 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Don't Use 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Nozzle is defect 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Line visible 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Nozzle is suspicious; maybe OK or maybe misdirecting 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Unknown 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Use 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Nozzle is OK 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">OK 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p ">. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After being classified for the next swath the following action are being taken dependent on: 
</p><ul id="UL_9AF6E154A754431EA2B76EE4C1FEBDBD" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_806B218A99054EFA8268E4D07F2D152D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">NFC classification: Use, Avoid, Don't Use 
</p></li><li id="LI_34BC1D7347F0452EAAC2E24A25C12872" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The selected Print mode 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-4AF4399C-A9A3-489B-B318-4875BD3C0E78" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The nozzle failure detection has intensively been improved so that the printer can better detect if a nozzle is working correctly or not. With a better detection also a better compensation is possible. 
</p></note><note id="GUID-7AB7C08E-826C-4B6C-9F49-8AD88A29C6E1" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> As mentioned in the previous note, the nozzle failure detection has intensively been improved for all print modes. In general the ability to compensate failing nozzles is better in higher quality print mode(s). 
</p></note><p class="- topic/p ">The engine-software chooses a specific compensation method. In general the following rules apply: 
</p><table id="M149114-TB177" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="stage" cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="75*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Print mode 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">General rules 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> ... (.. pass) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">No compensation / Nozzle failure compensation 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="M149114-B178" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Keep in mind that there might be a few situations where nozzle-outs still might be visible:</title><ul id="UL_C2DA179364EB4A568891005F9EF4F637" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_D20CA84F89F1431BAD7090693BA06BFE" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Nozzle Failure Compensation is reactive. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">First a nozzle has to fail before the engine is able to correct it. This might lead to 1 or 2 lines (white or colored). 
</p></li><li id="LI_EBDA00EADBDB4D849B6A6A489B54D248" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Not recognized failing nozzle. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The PAINt algorithm is not perfect. Some times failing nozzle are not recognized. Usually these are misdirecting nozzles. In such a case no compensation will take place. Therefore the customer can run the Automatic maintenance on the Operator Panel. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">In all these cases a reprint of the file or choosing temporarily another print mode is advised as a first step since it might resolve the issue. 
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-DED869E2-6BF4-4A33-A12A-F3C8CD878DCF.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
